==English==
=== Etymology ===
[[New Latin]], from {{L.}} [[septicus]] + New Latin [[-emia]]

===Alternative spellings===
* [[septicaemia]]

===Noun===
'''septicemia'''

# {{pathology}} A disease caused by the prescence of pathogenic organisms, especially [[bacterium|bacteria]], or their toxins, in the [[bloodstream]], characterised by chills and fever.

====Synonyms====
* [[blood poisoning]]
* [[septic fever]]

